The '''Gladstone Professorship of Government''' is located at [[All Souls College]] at the [[University of Oxford]]. It was instituted in memory of [[William Ewart Gladstone]]. The professorship has never been held by a woman. Its past holders have been:
* [[Sir Kenneth Clinton Wheare]], 1944-1956 <ref> {{citation|url=http://adb.anu.edu.au/biography/wheare-sir-kenneth-clinton-12005 |title=Wheare, Sir Kenneth Clinton (1907–1979) |accessdate=2012-06-08}}</ref> * [[Max Beloff]], 1957-1974 * [[Samuel Finer]], 1974-1982 <ref> {{citation|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/obituary-professor-samuel-finer-1490939.html |title=Obituary: Professor Samuel Finer |accessdate=2012-06-08 | location=London |work=The Independent |first=Dennis |last=Kavanagh |date=1993-06-11}}</ref> * [[Peter Pulzer]], 1985-1996 <ref> {{citation|url=http://www.all-souls.ox.ac.uk/people.php?personid=227| title=Professor Peter Pulzer |accessdate=2012-06-08}}</ref> * [[Alfred C. Stepan]], 1996-1999 before he re-joined [[Columbia University]] <ref>{{citation|url=http://www.ox.ac.uk/gazette/1999-00/weekly/040500/news/story_3.htm| title=New Gladstone Professor of Government| work=Oxford University Gazette| date=4 May 2000| accessdate=31 January 2012}}</ref> * [[Christopher Hood]], 2001-2014. He worked mainly on executive government and the politics of public services. * [[Stathis Kalyvas]], 2018- . <ref> {{citation|url=https://www.politics.ox.ac.uk/news/stathis-kalyvas-appointed-to-the-gladstone-professorship-of-government.html| title=Professor Stathis Kalyvas appointed to the Gladstone Professorship of Government|accessdate=22 January 2018}}</ref>
