{{infobox person/Wikidata | fetchwikidata=ALL}}
'''Harald Bjørlykke''' (14 September 1901 &ndash; 28 February 1968) was a Norwegian geologist.

He was born in [[Ås, Akershus|Ås]], a son of [[Knut Olai Bjørlykke]].<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Harald Bjørlykke|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/Harald_Bj%C3%B8rlykke|language=Norwegian|accessdate=16 January 2010}}</ref> He was the father of [[Arne Bjørlykke]].<ref>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Arne Bjørlykke|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/Arne_Bj%C3%B8rlykke|language=Norwegian|accessdate=16 January 2010}}</ref>

He took the [[dr.philos.]] degree in 1935, and mainly worked within [[mineralogy]] and the [[ore|geology of ore]]. He was the director of [[Norsk Bergverk]] from 1958, director of the [[Norwegian Geological Survey]] from 1958 to 1966, and professor of geology at the [[Norwegian Institute of Technology]] from 1966 to his death.<ref name=snl/>

